<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 3:56PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN FRANKLIN AND
SOUTHEASTERN FULTON COUNTIES THROUGH 430 PM EDT...
At 356 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northeast of Hancock, moving south at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mercersburg, Big Cove Tannery, Claylick and Whitetail Ski Area.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
south central Pennsylvania.</instruction>
